        The practice of psionics is the mastering of mental power.  It
involves the disciplines of telepathy, teleportation, and extrasensory
perception.  Additionally, the psionicist learns to manipulate the minds
of his enemies to damage them or change their perceptions and alter the
characteristics of objects.  Psionicists stand in the center of their
own universes and alter the beings and objects around them to fit their
own conceptions.
        With mages, necromancers, druids, and clerics you may be asking
yourself 'Why psionicists?'.  The answer is that psionicists are unique,
with a style and philosophy quite distinct from other 'spellcasting'
guilds.  Psionicists do not call upon the forces of magic, of nature,
of the powers of Darkness, or the powers of Light.  Psionicists call
upon themselves.  They are masters of themselves and of their own minds.
Their power is a very individual thing, trained and developed in
different directions by each member of the Guild according to his or
her desires.
        The study of the mind is a rigorous path to follow but it offers
unparalleled opportunities for personal choice in character development.
The purpose of this document was simply to introduce the Guild to the
reader.  For in-depth information on the guild and how you can become a
member, visit the guild itself one east of the post office.  That's
S,S,S,S,W,W,S from Center of Town.
